Determines if the specified character is a letter or digit. *

* A character is considered to be a letter or digit if either * {@code Character.isLetter(char ch)} or * {@code Character.isDigit(char ch)} returns * {@code true} for the character. * *

Note: This method cannot handle supplementary characters. To support * all Unicode characters, including supplementary characters, use * the {@link #isLetterOrDigit(int)} method.
* A constant holding the minimum value an {@code int} can * have, -2<sup>31</sup>. */
